org.jeo.geom

Class CoordinatePath

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jeo.geom.CoordinatePath
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterator<com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Coordinate>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    EmptyPath, GeometryCollectionPath, LineStringPath, PointPath, PolygonPath

    public abstract class CoordinatePath
extends Object
implements Iterator<com.vividsolutions.jts.geom.Coordinate>
    A sequence or path of coordinates.

    As the path is traversed a step() is maintained that describes how the current coordinate relates to the previous coordinate.

    Author:
    Justin Deoliveira, OpenGeo

      • generalize

        public CoordinatePath generalize(double dx,
                        double dy)
        Specifies that the coordinate path should be generalized skipping coordinates that are close to one another.

        The dx and dy arguments are used as a tolerance to collapse coordinates. Consecutive coordinates with both horizontal and vertical distance less than dx and dy respectively are collapsed.

        Parameters:
        dx - Horizontal generalization distance, only taken into account when generalization is true
        dy - Vertical generalization distance, only taken into account when generalization is true
